Haven't eaten at McDonald's in quite some time. I must say the restaurant's new renovations look quite modern and nice. They even have a table designated for handicapped, the restaurant is wheelchair accessible. Bathroom is extra large, not sure why they didn't create two stalls. The water pressure barely comes out. I downloaded the app for time constraints. It doesn't charge your card until you  type of transaction, pick up, eating in etc. But, if you want to add or remove part of your order the staff didn't seem to know how. So, they just gave me a large order of fries for free, that was a nice courtesy. Other than that, they app worked great. I received my food after providing my order number. I ordered Chicken McNugget meal. The Chicken McNuggets were over cooked and the fries were i a large size box. But, the actual amount given was a medium fry and, it didn't quite fill the box it's packaged in. I saw this after I stood the box up on my tray. I was sharing them with someone else. The fries were fresh. But, something unusual occured, they had no taste. I ordered a Peach Lemonade Slushie, made by Minute Made. It was over the top sweet. After eating my meal and letting the drink sit, it toned down the sweetness. I was able to drink it and enjoy the taste. The restaurant was full with nice spacing between tables, and bench seating. A table full of young people was in the rear. Near the door was a table full of older women having a chat. Party of two and single patrons was represented well. Great relaxed, semi quiet atmosphere. Observed friendly staff extending themselves to the patrons, bringing them their food with a smile or making suggestions. I won't be back anytie soon. But, it made a nice impression on me.
